_The naming system, that Adobe uses, violates the OT specification, but it works. So the consistency check reports errors, as far as I remember._  
&nbsp;  
It is unclear to me what you mean; the _Consistency Checker_ in DTL OTMaster checks the naming against the OT specs, it even summarizes the specs.  
&nbsp;  
_how fast you can update the OTMaster, when Adobe updates the AFDKO_  
&nbsp;  
OTM is used internally at URW++ and DTL for the daily production. When a new version of the AFDKO becomes available, it is built in almost immediately.  
&nbsp;  
_I would be interested in a light version (not the test version) without the glyph editor. I assume, that it would be easy to remove it. Can you imagine to provide such a version for less money?_  
&nbsp;  
Nope, tailor made versions are actually more expensive.  
&nbsp;  
The simple thing with pricing is, that if one considers a product to be too expensive, one should not buy it.
